Can be considered a 'wrapper' around a VM. Node passes the JS to the 
VM and gets the results back. It csn be thought of as a 'co-ordinator' for
this process.

Node also comes with some built in modules, making it very useful.

Node also offers built in Asynchronous APIs!

There is also C++ Addon support

Node also has a built in package manager, NPM
and a module dependency managerv (common JS)



When using Node REPL, the .editor command
will allow us to write multiline code easily.
Simply type ctrl+D to exit it when done

There are many other options like this. type
.help in REPL